    <p> We were lucky this morning. The good part was we promptly found a quiet and free parking space and the one close to my office. So we were able to use the toilet and showers there. Unfortunately, the weather didn't really play along. It looked like rain all day and one or the other time it started to drip very easily. </p>
    <p> When we were finally finished with showers and moving, we went to the city on foot to ask for help for Steffi's camera in the Sony Store. Unfortunately, the lady could not help us in sales and the service center on the first floor does not have an up today. So come back tomorrow and try again. </p>
    <p> From there we wanted to take the free bus to Circular Quay. Unfortunately this did not come and since we didn't feel like waiting for longer, we took a normal bus there. Once in the harbor, we got the incredibly expensive tickets for the Taronga Zoo. These cost $ 55, which is converted to around &euro; 45. With these tickets we were then at least allowed to go to the zoo by ferry. </p>
    <p> When we arrived at the zoo, the sun had crazy strength. Personally it was a little uncomfortable, but I think Steffi was very happy to finally get a little sun again. We looked around very comfortably in the zoo and spent some time with the locals such as Koalas, Reptiles and Kangaroos. I had finally seen it with giraffes and hippos with my own eyes because I only knew these animals from TV. </p>
