    <p> Unfortunately, the later afternoon sustained and it started to dribble a little. Since the zoo, like all other sights, closes on time at 5 p.m., we had initially decided to move further and take photos of Sydney's skyline. Unfortunately, the clouds became thicker and more and more smelled of rain. When we arrived at the ferry, we even had to slip back into our jackets, since unfortunately the wind was getting colder and colder. </p>
    <p> We decided to move the walk across the Harbor Bridge and the skyline photos to the next day and prefer to eat something somewhere. After long back and forth we decided to go back to Chinatown and ended up in a mile. In the middle of the tables and chairs and an Asiastate next to the other. </p>
    <p> The food was good, cheap and of course Asian again. On the way back to the car, it unfortunately started to really rain. We just decided quickly and then go straight to bed, in the hope that the rain will lie down overnight so that we can walk over the Harbor Bridge the next day in good weather. </p>
